A man, believed to be in his 20s, drowned while fishing with friends in the Duzi River in Scottsville in Pietermaritzburg on Saturday night, KwaZulu-Natal paramedics said. ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene at about 7.15pm and were greeted by a number of the man s friends, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said. They informed paramedics that they had been fishing in the river when the missing man jumped in the water and attempted to swim across. South African Police Service (SAPS) water rescue officers arrived on the scene and began to search the banks for the missing man. After some time the man s body was found along the banks. Unfortunately, it was evident that the man had been dead for some time. Nothing could be done for the man and he was declared dead on the scene, Meiring said. African News Agency (ANA)